function loadPlayerAssets()
    -- init the player_assets table, used
    player_assets = {}
    for color, their_asset_guids in pairs(ASSET_GUIDS) do
        player_assets[color] = {}
        for asset, guid in pairs(their_asset_guids) do
            if asset == 'snaps' or asset == 'last_dealt_slot' or asset == 'rotation' then
                player_assets[color][asset] = guid
            else
                player_assets[color][asset] = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
            end
        end
    end
end

function onLoad()
    mode = "poker"
    -- clear out the stupid default playlist
    MusicPlayer.setPlaylist({})
    -- load the most common objects from GUIDs
    loadPlayerAssets()
    
    dice_text = getObjectFromGUID(DICE_TEXT)
    dice_board = getObjectFromGUID(DICE_BOARD_GUID)
    deck = getDeck()
    pot = getObjectFromGUID(POT_GUID)
    pot_text = {
        getObjectFromGUID('8e0d31'),
        getObjectFromGUID('bd6e01'),
        getObjectFromGUID('0a85cf'),
        getObjectFromGUID('82117f')
    }
    -- this the button the dirty way, rather than using XML
    local button = getObjectFromGUID(COIN_GUID)
    button.createButton({
        function_owner=self,
        click_function = 'stack',
        position = {0, 0.1, 0},
        width = 900,
        height = 900,
        label = 'reset',
        font_size = 250
    })

    -- set up flashy winning chip array
    flashy = {}
    color_idx = 1
    all_colors = {}
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        table.insert(all_colors, color)
    end
end

function getCardRotation()
    local card = getObjectFromGUID('4791ba')
    print(card.getRotation())
end

function onExternalMessage(message)
    deck = getDeck()
    if message.method == 'dealToTable' then
        if player_assets[message.color] then
            dealToTable(message.color)
        end 
    end
    if message.method == 'dealToHand' then
        if Player[message.color].seated then
            deck.deal(1, message.color)
        end
    end
    if message.method == "ante" then
        ante()
    end
    if message.method == 'dealBaseball' then
        deck = getDeck()
        dealBaseball()
    end
    if message.method == 'dealPTT' then
        deck = getDeck()
        deck.deal(7)
    end
    if message.method == 'end' then
        stack()
    end
    if message.method == 'scores' then
        submitScores()
    end
end

function dealToTable(toColor)
    card_snap_num = (player_assets[toColor].last_dealt_slot + 1)
    if card_snap_num <5 then
        deck.takeObject({
            position=player_assets[toColor].snaps[card_snap_num],
            rotation={0, player_assets[toColor].rotation, 180},
            callback_function = function(obj) obj.flip() end
        })
    else
        deck.deal(1, toColor)
    end
    player_assets[toColor].last_dealt_slot = card_snap_num
end

function dealBaseball()
    deck.deal(2)
    for idx, color in pairs(getSeatedPlayers()) do
        dealToTable(color)
    end
end

function ante()
    for idx, color in pairs(getSeatedPlayers()) do
        player_assets[color].bag.takeObject({
            position={0,2,0},
        })
    end
end

function submitScores()
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        if isActivePlayer(color) then
            player_bag = player_assets[color].bag
            local data = {
                color=color,
                score=(getBagChipCount(player_bag)*0.25),
                steam_id=Player[color].steam_id
            }
            WebRequest.post('http://localhost:5000/scores/', data)
        end
    end
end

function onUpdate()
    renderFlashyObjects()
end

function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, obj)
    handleScriptingZoneEvent(zone,obj)
end

function onObjectLeaveScriptingZone(zone, obj)
    handleScriptingZoneEvent(zone,obj)
end

function onPlayerChangeColor(color)
    hideUnusedColors()
    if color ~= 'Grey' then
        postPlayerAPI(color)
    end
end

function onObjectPeek(object, player_color)
    if object.name == 'Card' or object.name == 'Deck' then
        if getColor(object) ~= player_color then
            playSoundClip('hey')
            broadcastToAll(string.format('%s is peeking at cards, is he cheating???',Player[player_color].steam_name))
        end
    end
end

function onObjectPickUp(player_color, picked_up_object)
    handleWinningChipPickup(player_color, picked_up_object)
    -- yell at players touch chips that aren't theirs
    if picked_up_object.getName() == 'chip' then
        if getColor(picked_up_object) ~= player_color then
            playSoundClip('hey')
        end
    end
end

function playSoundClip(clip_name)
    parameters = {
        url=MP3[clip_name],
        title=clip_name
    }
    MusicPlayer.setCurrentAudioclip(parameters)
    MusicPlayer.play()
    -- Wait.time(function() MusicPlayer.play() end, 1)
end

function handleScriptingZoneEvent(zone, obj)
    -- only watch for chips entering and leaving the pot, ignore other objects and zones
    if zone.guid == pot.guid then
        if obj.getName() == 'chip' then
            Wait.time(function() update_pot_totals(obj) end, 0.5)
        end
    end
end

function setFlashyObjects(object_name)
    for idx, object in ipairs(getAllObjectsByName(object_name)) do
        table.insert(flashy, object)
    end
end

function renderFlashyObjects()
    if #flashy > 0 then
        for idx, object in ipairs(flashy) do
            object.setColorTint(all_colors[color_idx])
        end
        color_idx = color_idx + 1
        if color_idx > #all_colors then
            color_idx = 1
        end
    end
end

function getAllObjectsByName(object_name)
    local objects = {}
    for idx, obj in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if obj.getName() == object_name then
            table.insert(objects, obj)
        end
    end
    return objects
end

function handleWinningChipPickup(player_color, picked_up_object)
    this_object_name = picked_up_object.getName()
    if this_object_name == 'winning_chip' or this_object_name == 'winning_chip_high' or this_object_name == 'winning_chip_low' then
        -- stop flashing all of that name type once claimed by a color 
        --- if you don't do this it spits out errors when added to a bag
        flashy = {}
        for idx, chip in ipairs(getAllObjectsByName(this_object_name)) do
            chip.setColorTint(player_color)
            chip.setName('chip')
            playSoundClip('john2')
        end
        -- keep the others flashy though
        setFlashyObjects('winning_chip')
        setFlashyObjects('winning_chip_high')
        setFlashyObjects('winning_chip_low')
    end
end

function onObjectEnterContainer(container, obj)
    if container.name == 'Bag' then
        updatePlayerFunds(container)
    end
end

function onObjectLeaveContainer(container, obj)
    if container.name == 'Bag' then
        if obj.getName() == 'winning_chip' then
            obj.setName('chip')
        end
        obj.setColorTint(container.getColorTint())
        updatePlayerFunds(container)
        -- update score
        
        local player_color = getColor(container)
        local data = {
            score=(getBagChipCount(container)*0.25),
            color=player_color,
            steam_id=Player[player_color].steam_id
        }
        -- putScoreAPI(Player[player_color].steam_name, data)        
    end
end

function format_currency(number_of_chips)
    return string.format("$%.2f", (number_of_chips * 0.25))
end

function getColor(obj)
    return obj.getColorTint():toString()
end

function update_pot_totals(chip)
    update_total_text()
    update_player_ping_text(chip)
end

function update_total_text()
    -- get the length of the chips in the pot array, convert to currency text
    local text = format_currency(#getPotChips())
    -- update the pot total text fields
    for idx, text_label in ipairs(pot_text) do
        text_label.setValue(text)
    end
end

function update_player_ping_text(trigger_chip)
    -- determine the color of the chip that triggered this function
    local trigger_chip_color = getColor(trigger_chip)

    -- count how many other chips are in the pot of this same color
    local count = 0
    for idx, chip in ipairs(getPotChips()) do
        if getColor(chip) == trigger_chip_color then
            count = count + 1
        end
    end

    -- format the string, update that colors contribution text
    local text = ' '
    if count > 0 then
        text = string.format('%d of ping', count)
    end
    player_assets[trigger_chip_color].pings.setValue(text)
end

function getBagChipCount(bag)
    -- count the chips in the bag, ignore other objects
    local bag_count = 0
    for idx, object in ipairs(bag.getObjects()) do
        if object.name == "chip" then
            bag_count = bag_count + 1
        end
    end
    return bag_count
end

function updatePlayerFunds(bag, obj)
    -- get the total funds text object for this bag color and update the value
    player_assets[getColor(bag)].total.setValue(format_currency(getBagChipCount(bag)))
end

function putScoreAPI(player, data)
    local url = string.format('%s/api/scores/%s', BASE_URL, player)
    WebRequest.put(url, JSON.encode(data), function(a) log(JSON.encode_pretty(JSON.decode(a.text))) end)
end

function postPlayerAPI(color)
    data = {
        player=Player[color].steam_name
    }
    local url = string.format('%s/api/scores/', BASE_URL)
    WebRequest.post(url, data, function(a) log(JSON.encode_pretty(JSON.decode(a.text))) end)
end

function getPotChips()
    -- loop over all objects in the pot, return only the chip objects
    local chips = {}
    for idx, object in ipairs(pot.getObjects()) do
        if object.getName() == 'chip' or object.getName() == 'winning_chip' then
            table.insert(chips, object)
        end
    end
    return chips
end

function getActivePlayerColors()
    -- loop over all players in the game, return their colors
    local colors = {}
    for idx, player in pairs(Player.getPlayers()) do
        colors[player.color] = 1
    end
    return colors
end

function isActivePlayer(this_color)
    -- for a given color, returns whether or not a player is using that color
    local ret_val = false
    for player_color,_ in pairs(getActivePlayerColors()) do
        if player_color == this_color then
            ret_val = true
        end
    end
    return ret_val
end

function getColorsExceptThisOne(this_color)
    -- for a given color, return a table of all colors except this one
    local the_other_colors = {}
    for color,_ in pairs(player_assets) do
        if color ~= this_color then
            table.insert(the_other_colors, color)
        end
    end
    return the_other_colors
end

function hideUnusedColors()
    hideUnusedColorsText()
    hideOtherColorsBags()
end

function hideUnusedColorsText()
    -- hide text labels for each player color if they are not in use
    local active_colors_kv = getActivePlayerColors()
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        if active_colors_kv[color] == nil then
            assets.total.setValue(' ')
            assets.pings.setValue(' ')
        end
    end
end

function hideOtherColorsBags()
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        assets.bag.setInvisibleTo(getColorsExceptThisOne(color))
    end
end

function resetPings()
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        assets.pings.setValue(' ')
    end
end

function stack()
    resetPings()
    -- postLocalPlayers()
    local buffer = 1.25
    local total = 0
    local stack_num = 0
    local row_num = 0
    local x = -0.5
    local y = 1
    local z = 1
    local chipsPresent = false
    for _,o in ipairs(getPotChips()) do
        chipsPresent = true
        z = -z
        total = total + 1
        stack_num = stack_num + 1
        y = y + 0.5
        slowMove(o,{x,y,z})
        if stack_num >= 8 then
            stack_num = 0
            row_num = row_num + 1
            y = 1
            x = x + buffer
            if row_num >= 5 then
                row_num = 0
                x = -0.5
                z = z + buffer
            end
        end
        -- designate this a winning chip and make it flashy
        table.insert(flashy, o)
        ptt = true
        if ptt then
            o.setName('winning_chip_low')
            if z < 0 then
                o.setName('winning_chip_high')
            end
        else
            o.setName('winning_chip')
        end
    end
    if chipsPresent then
        playSoundClip('john1')
    end
    -- return all cards to the deck and shuffle it up
    shuffle()
end

function shuffle()
    -- rotate and reposition all cards or decks currently on the table 
    -- this will form decks by merging them
    for idx, object in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if object.name == "Card" or object.name =="Deck" then
            object.setRotationSmooth({180,45,0}, false, true)
            Wait.time(function() object.setPositionSmooth({8,2.5,8}, false, false) end, 2)
        end
    end
    -- wait and then put all hands into the newly formed deck
    -- Wait.time(function() returnHandCards() end, 3)
    Wait.time(function()
        -- discover the deck on the table
        local this_deck = nil
        for idx, object in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
            if object.name =="Deck" then
                this_deck = object
            end
        end
        -- for each card in any player's hands, move to the deck
        if this_deck then
            for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
                for idx, object in ipairs(Player[color].getHandObjects()) do
                    if object.name =="Card" then
                        this_deck.putObject(object)
                    end
                end
            end
        end
        -- once all cards have returned, shuffle it a few times
        Wait.time(function() this_deck.shuffle() end, 1.5)
        Wait.time(function() this_deck.shuffle() end, 1.75)
        Wait.time(function() this_deck.shuffle() end, 2)
        Wait.time(function() this_deck.shuffle() end, 2.25)
        -- set this as the deck so other functions can use it
        deck = this_deck
        resetDealtPositions()
    end, 3)
end

function getDeck()
    local this_deck = nil
    for idx, object in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if object.name =="Deck" then
            this_deck = object
        end
    end
    return this_deck
end

function resetDealtPositions()
    for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
        assets.last_dealt_slot = 0
    end
end 

function returnHandCards()
    -- discover the deck on the table
    local deck = nil
    for idx, object in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if object.name =="Deck" then
            deck = object
        end
    end
    -- for each card in any player's hands, move to the deck
    if deck then
        for color, assets in pairs(player_assets) do
            for idx, object in ipairs(Player[color].getHandObjects()) do
                if object.name =="Card" then
                    deck.putObject(object)
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

function slowMove(object, vector)
    -- re-orients object, waits, and then moves object
    object.setRotationSmooth({0,0,0}, false, true)
    Wait.time(function() object.setPositionSmooth(vector, false, true) end, 1)
    Wait.time(function() object.setPositionSmooth(vector, false, true) end, 3)
end

function pay(params)
    local above_chip = params.position
    above_chip[2] = above_chip[2] + params.offset
    player_assets[params.bank].bag.takeObject({
        position=params.position
    })
end

function sweep(params)
    player_assets[params.bank].bag.putObject(params.chip)
end


function toggleGameMode()
    deck = getDeck()
    if mode == "poker" then
        mode = "dice"
        dice_board.setPositionSmooth({0,1.27,0}, false, false)
        dice_board.setRotationSmooth({0, 135, 0}, false, false)
        deck.setPositionSmooth({-5.5,2.5,-5.5}, false, false)
        deck.setRotationSmooth({180,135,0}, false, false)
    else
        mode = "poker"
        dice_text.setValue(' ')
        dice_board.setPositionSmooth({0,-20,0}, false, false)
        Wait.time(function() dice_board.setRotationSmooth({180, 135, 0}, false, false) end, 1)
        
        deck.setPositionSmooth({8,2.5,8}, false, false)
        deck.setRotationSmooth({180,45,0}, false, false)
    end
    UI.setAttributes("game_mode", {textColor="white", text=mode})
end

SURFACE_GUID = 'fd28b3'
BOARD_GUID = 'fd28b3'
NORMAL_TEXT_COLOR = "#CCCCCC"
LOSE_TEXT_COLOR = "#666666"
WIN_TEXT_COLOR = "#00FF99"
DICE_TEXT = "53ef73"

function onLoad()
    dice_text = getObjectFromGUID(DICE_TEXT)
    board = getObjectFromGUID(BOARD_GUID)
    betting_areas = {
        high={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('8c0f12')},
        low={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('0dbb7c')},
        even={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('988d4d')},
        odd={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('731116')},
        [1]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('17dc57')},
        [2]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('0f4d53')},
        [3]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('8f0c9d')},
        [4]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('f64e85')},
        [5]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('337830')},
        [6]={pay=0, obj=getObjectFromGUID('ad3979')}
    }
end

function colorAll(color)
    for xml_id,_ in pairs(betting_areas) do
        self.UI.setAttributes(xml_id, {color=color})
    end
end

function reset()
    -- for idx, die in ipairs(getObjectsWithTag("dice")) do
    --     die.setColorTint("Red")
    -- end
    colorAll(NORMAL_TEXT_COLOR)
    self.UI.setAttributes("sum", {color=NORMAL_TEXT_COLOR})
    self.UI.setValue("sum", "__")
    self.UI.setAttributes("payout", {interactable="false", textColor=LOSE_TEXT_COLOR})
end

function incrementPayout(this_area)
    betting_areas[this_area].pay = betting_areas[this_area].pay + 1
end

function updateBoard()
    colorAll(LOSE_TEXT_COLOR)
    
    local win_attibutes = {
        color=WIN_TEXT_COLOR
    }

    local sum = 0
    for idx, die in ipairs(getObjectsWithTag("dice")) do
        local die_value = die.getValue()
        sum = sum + die_value
        self.UI.setAttributes(die_value, win_attibutes)
        incrementPayout(die_value)
    end
    
    self.UI.setAttributes("sum", {color=WIN_TEXT_COLOR})
    self.UI.setValue("sum", sum)

    if sum < 10 then
        incrementPayout("low")
        self.UI.setAttributes("low", win_attibutes)
    else
        incrementPayout("high")
        self.UI.setAttributes("high", win_attibutes)
    end

    if sum % 2 == 0 then
        incrementPayout("even")
        self.UI.setAttributes("even", win_attibutes)
    else
        incrementPayout("odd")
        self.UI.setAttributes("odd", win_attibutes)
    end

end


function score()
    -- reset previous score
    for name, values in pairs(betting_areas) do
        values.pay = 0
    end
    updateBoard()
    self.UI.setAttributes("payout", {interactable="true", textColor=NORMAL_TEXT_COLOR})
end

function payout(playerWhoClicked)
    local scores = {}
    for idx,color in ipairs(getSeatedPlayers()) do
        -- local tmp = {}
        -- for area, _ in pairs(betting_areas) do
        --     tmp[area] = 0.0
        -- end
        scores[color] = 0.0
    end
    local bank_color = playerWhoClicked.color
    local bank_score = 0
    for name, values in pairs(betting_areas) do
        objects_in_area = values.obj.getObjects()
        for idx, object in ipairs(objects_in_area) do
            if object.getName() == 'chip' then
                chip_color = object.getColorTint():toString()
                
                local height = 1
                for i=1,values.pay do
                    Global.call("pay", {
                        bank=bank_color,
                        position=object.getPosition(),
                        offset = height
                    })
                    height = height + 1
                    scores[chip_color] = scores[chip_color] + 0.25
                    bank_score = bank_score - 0.25
                end
                if values.pay == 0 then
                    Global.call("sweep", {
                        bank=bank_color,
                        chip=object
                    })
                    scores[chip_color] = scores[chip_color] - 0.25
                    bank_score = bank_score + 0.25
                end
            end
        end
    end

    local text = {string.format('%s as bank this round: $%.2f', playerWhoClicked.steam_name, bank_score)}
    for idx,color in ipairs(getSeatedPlayers()) do
        local total = scores[color]
        if color == bank_color then

        elseif total > 0 then
            table.insert(text, string.format('%s won $%.2f', Player[color].steam_name, total))
        elseif total < 0 then
            table.insert(text, string.format('%s lost $%.2f', Player[color].steam_name, total))
        else 
            table.insert(text, string.format('%s broke even', Player[color].steam_name, total))
        end
        scores[color] = 0.0
    end
    text = table.concat(text, "\n")
    dice_text.setValue(text)

    self.UI.setAttributes("payout", {interactable="false", textColor=LOSE_TEXT_COLOR})

end
